

@host = http://localhost:3000
@phone = +5511977777777
@uuid = meu-device-123

### 1) Login com telefone novo -> 202 (envia SMS). Em modo dev volta "devCode".
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}",
  "uuid": "{{uuid}}"
}

### 2) Confirmar -> 200 (cria/ativa o usuario). Troque CODE pelo codigo recebido.
POST {{host}}/users/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}",
  "uuid": "{{uuid}}",
  "code": "CODE"
}

### 3) Login de novo com o MESMO uuid -> 200 (login direto, devolve o usuario).
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}",
  "uuid": "{{uuid}}"
}

### 4) Login com uuid DIFERENTE -> 202 (precisa confirmar de novo).
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "{{phone}}",
  "uuid": "outro-device-999"
}

### 5) Confirmar com telefone/uuid sem codigo enviado -> 404.
POST {{host}}/users/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+5511900000000",
  "uuid": "qualquer",
  "code": "123456"
}

### 6) Preencher os demais dados do usuario -> 200. Troque 1 pelo id do usuario.
PUT {{host}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Kaio",
  "description": "Aluno de Mobile",
  "email": "kaio@example.com"
}

### 7) Buscar usuario por id (auxiliar).
GET {{host}}/users/1
